<br>
My advise has to be to not get too hung up on what other people think of your class.  After 4 years of class balancing or so, things are close enough that everyone has a job, or should be able to find one, unless they really don't understand what they are playing at all.  Play your class because youi enjoy it, not because someone just told you how great they ate.  If the only reason you are happy with being a ranger is because the last guy told you how great they are, the next time someone tells you they suck you are going to be unhappy again.  Find some class to be happy with for it's own sake, ranger or otherwise.<br>
<br>
